to update the python package :

run from root 'Diplotocus' folder
rm -rf build/ dist/ *.egg-info
#next step is very important, generates automatic docstring from matplotlib.
#core.py imports the generated py file, so if not ran, any newly added class will not appear in the package
python3 diplotocus/generate_doc_api.py
FILES TO UPDATE THE VERSION:
    -PYPROJECT.TOML
    -diplotocus/_version.py
    -README.MD (GITHUB BADGE)
python3 -m build
twine upload dist/*
(token is in ~/.pypirc)

to update the docs :

run from Neural-Network-Stellar-Ages/NEST/nest-docs
DO NOT run jupyter-book clean ., it messes up the github
if you did, delete repo, start a new one from github desktop, name it html and select the _build folder so it just takes
all the files directly from it, and create a .nojekyll file so the _ in the url are not broken
jupyter-book build --all .
push to the NEST-docs repo